article.headline: S. Carolina St. 72, Hampton 60
article.story: ORANGEBURG, S.C. -- Jason Flagler scored 22 points and Arsenio Williams had 16 as South Carolina State defeated Hampton 72-60 on Saturday. A jumper by Flagler, who made 9 of 12 shots, started the Bulldogs (12-8, 6-3 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) on a 13-2 second-half run that gave them a 51-37 lead with 13:06 remaining. The Bulldogs led by as many as 17 points, 58-41, with 9:34 left and never by less than eight points the rest of the way. South Carolina State opened a 25-13 lead in the first half but Vince Simpson, who led the Pirates (6-15, 4-6) with 19 points, scored 14 of them during a 14-1 run that gave Hampton a 27-26 lead. The Bulldogs scored the final six points of the first half to lead 34-29 at intermission. Led by Williams, South Carolina State's bench outscored Hampton's 33-6.
